# Keep the build context lean: the service Dockerfiles only COPY services/lib
# and their own service dir, and every image runs `uv sync` to build its own
# environment — so host virtualenvs, caches, and VCS metadata are pure bloat
# (and baking a host .venv into the image would ship the wrong-arch wheels).
**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
.git
.gitignore
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/node_modules
**/*.zarr
**/tmp.zarr
**/scripts/figures
.config
*.env
.env
**/.DS_Store
